{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857967150,"sessionID":"ses_2869e55eeffeo9snU5NGcsmYPh","part":{"id":"prt_d79621cba001IbUSf70PoPfNkl","messageID":"msg_d79620ed40019n2Pn2A3CTst36","sessionID":"ses_2869e55eeffeo9snU5NGcsmYPh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8b6d78e88d504b1b897ff763","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/picod  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: Configuration (auth_config.go)\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Create `pkg/picod/auth_config.go` with `AuthConfig` struct containing:\n15:   - `PublicKeyPath` string (optional, for file-based key loading)\n16:   - `PublicPaths` []string (comma-separated paths exempt from auth)\n17:   - `AllowQueryParam` bool (enable token via ?token=)\n18:   - `JWTIssuer` string (expected issuer claim)\n19:   - `JWTAudience` string (expected audience claim)\n20: \n21: - [ ] **T002** Add environment variable loading functions:\n22:   - `LoadAuthConfigFromEnv() (*AuthConfig, error)`\n23:   - `GetPublicPathsFromEnv() []string`\n24:   - `GetBoolEnv(key string, defaultValue bool) bool`\n25: \n26: - [ ] **T003** Add validation for AuthConfig (Validate() error)\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ### Phase 2: Enhanced Middleware (auth_middleware.go)\n31: \n32: - [ ] **T010** Create `pkg/picod/auth_middleware.go` with enhanced middleware:\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T011** Implement public path checking:\n35:   - `isPublicPath(path string, publicPaths []string) bool`\n36: \n37: - [ ] **T012** Implement query parameter token extraction:\n38:   - Extract token from `?token=` query parameter when enabled\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T013** Implement issuer/audience validation:\n41:   - Validate `iss` claim if configured\n42:   - Validate `aud` claim if configured\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T014** Implement error response standardization:\n45:   - Add `error_code` field to error responses\n46:   - Match pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go patterns\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ### Phase 3: AuthManager Enhancements (auth.go)\n51: \n52: - [ ] **T020** Add dynamic public key reload method:\n53:   - `ReloadPublicKey() error` - reload from environment variable\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T021** Add SIGHUP signal handler support:\n56:   - `StartKeyRotationWatcher()` - listen for SIGHUP and reload key\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T022** Add error code constants:\n59:   - `ErrCodeMissingHeader = \"AUTH_MISSING_HEADER\"`\n60:   - `ErrCodeInvalidFormat = \"AUTH_INVALID_FORMAT\"`\n61:   - `ErrCodeInvalidToken = \"AUTH_INVALID_TOKEN\"`\n62:   - `ErrCodeTokenExpired = \"AUTH_TOKEN_EXPIRED\"`\n63:   - `ErrCodeKeyNotConfigured = \"AUTH_KEY_NOT_CONFIGURED\"`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### Phase 4: Server Integration (server.go)\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T030** Update `NewServer()` to accept AuthConfig parameter\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T031** Update route registration to use public paths:\n72:   - Configure `/health` as public by default\n73:   - Apply public path filter in middleware\n74: \n75: - [ ] **T032** Register SIGHUP handler for key rotation\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ### Phase 5: Testing (auth_config_test.go, auth_middleware_test.go)\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T040** Create `pkg/picod/auth_config_test.go`:\n82:   - Test LoadAuthConfigFromEnv with valid config\n83:   - Test LoadAuthConfigFromEnv with missing required fields\n84:   - Test GetPublicPathsFromEnv parsing\n85:   - Test GetBoolEnv with various values\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T041** Create `pkg/picod/auth_middleware_test.go`:\n88:   - Test isPublicPath matching\n89:   - Test query parameter token extraction\n90:   - Test issuer/audience validation\n91:   - Test error response format with error_code\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T042** Update existing `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`:\n94:   - Add tests for ReloadPublicKey()\n95:   - Add tests for SIGHUP key rotation\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### Phase 6: Build & Verify\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T050** Run `go build ./cmd/picod` - verify build succeeds\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T051** Run `go test ./pkg/picod/...` - verify all unit tests pass\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T052** Run `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` - verify no vet errors\n106: \n107: - [ ] **T053** Run `golint ./pkg/picod/...` (if configured) - verify linting\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## Dependencies\n112: \n113: - **T001**: None (new file)\n114: - **T002**: T001\n115: - **T010**: T001, T002\n116: - **T011**: T010\n117: - **T012**: T010\n118: - **T013**: T010\n119: - **T014**: T010\n120: - **T020**: auth.go (existing)\n121: - **T021**: T020\n122: - **T022**: T020\n123: - **T030**: T010, T014\n124: - **T031**: T030\n125: - **T032**: T021\n126: - **T040**: T002\n127: - **T041**: T010\n128: - **T042**: T020\n129: - **T050**: All implementation tasks\n130: - **T051**: T040, T041, T042\n131: - **T052**: T050\n132: - **T053**: T050\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Configuration Variables\n137: \n138: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n139: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n140: | PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY | Yes | - | PEM-encoded RSA public key |\n141: | PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_PATHS | No | /health | Comma-separated paths that skip auth |\n142: | PICOD_AUTH_ALLOW_QUERY_PARAM | No | false | Enable token via ?token= query param |\n143: | PICOD_JWT_ISSUER | No | - | Expected JWT issuer claim |\n144: | PICOD_JWT_AUDIENCE | No | - | Expected JWT audience claim |\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## References\n149: \n150: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md`\n151: - Proposal: `proposal.md` (AR-017)\n152: - Existing: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n153: - Existing: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n154: - Reference: `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go`\n\n(End of file - total 154 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Configuration (auth_config.go)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `pkg/picod/auth_config.go` with `AuthConfig` struct containing:\n  - `PublicKeyPath` string (optional, for file-based key loading)\n  - `PublicPaths` []string (comma-separated paths exempt from auth)\n  - `AllowQueryParam` bool (enable token via ?token=)\n  - `JWTIssuer` string (expected issuer claim)\n  - `JWTAudience` string (expected audience claim)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775857967134,"end":1775857967148}}}}
